  "prompt": "What are the comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations:\n\n1. United States\n- Comprehensive legal framework under Bank Secrecy Act and USA PATRIOT Act\n- Strict reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Aggressive criminal prosecution\n- Substantial penalties and asset forfeiture\n\n2. European Union\n- Unified Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Harmonized regulatory approach across member states\n- Enhanced due diligence requirements\n- Focus on international cooperation\n\n3. United Kingdom\n- Proceeds of Crime Act\n- Risk-based supervision\n- Emphasis on financial intelligence\n- Strong international collaboration\n\n4. Switzerland\n- Traditionally known for banking secrecy\n- Recent reforms increasing transparency\n- Strict customer identification protocols\n- Significant penalties for non-compliance\n\n5. China\n- Centralized regulatory approach\n- Strict government oversight\n- Increasing international cooperation\n- Severe criminal penalties\n\n6. Russia\n- Developing legal framework\n- Inconsistent enforcement\n- Complex regulatory environment\n- Limited international transparency\n\n7. Singapore\n- Sophisticated regulatory system\n- Strict compliance requirements\n- Advanced technological monitoring\n- Significant financial penalties\n\nThese approaches demonstrate varying levels of regulatory complexity and enforcement mechanisms.",
